exports[`migrate > migrate 4 5 --format markdown 1`] = `
"# Migration Guide: antd v4 → v5

> 34 total steps: 19 auto-fixable, 15 manual

## Global

### Design token system replaces Less variables. All Less variable overrides must be migrated to CSS-in-JS tokens via ConfigProvider.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

1. Remove all Less variable overrides (modifyVars, less-loader theme config)
2. Wrap your app with ConfigProvider and pass a theme object
3. Map Less variables to Design Tokens (e.g. @primary-color → token.colorPrimary)
4. Remove babel-plugin-import if present (v5 supports tree-shaking natively)

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
// webpack.config.js or .umirc.ts
theme: { '@primary-color': '#1890ff' }

// or .less file
@import '~antd/dist/antd.less';
@primary-color: #1890ff;
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
import { ConfigProvider } from 'antd';
<ConfigProvider theme={{ token: { colorPrimary: '#1890ff' } }}>
  <App />
</ConfigProvider>
\`\`\`

**Reference:** https://ant.design/docs/react/migrate-less-variables

### Component styles no longer include CSS reset. Wrap app with <App /> component to restore.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

1. Import App component from antd
2. Wrap your root component with <App />
3. Use App.useApp() hook to access message, notification, modal instances

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
import { Button } from 'antd';

const MyApp = () => <Button>Click</Button>;
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
import { App, Button } from 'antd';

const MyApp = () => (
  <App>
    <Button>Click</Button>
  </App>
);
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`import\\s*\\{[^}]*\\}\\s*from\\s*['"]antd['"]\`

**Reference:** https://ant.design/components/app

### Moment.js replaced by Day.js. All date-related components (DatePicker, TimePicker, Calendar) now use Day.js.

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

1. Replace moment imports with dayjs
2. dayjs API is mostly compatible with moment
3. If you need locale support, import dayjs locale separately
4. If you need plugins (isBetween, etc.), import and extend dayjs

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
import moment from 'moment';
<DatePicker value={moment('2024-01-01')} />
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
import dayjs from 'dayjs';
<DatePicker value={dayjs('2024-01-01')} />
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`import\\s+moment\\s+from\\s+['"]moment['"]\`

### babel-plugin-import is no longer needed. antd v5 supports tree-shaking natively.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

1. Remove babel-plugin-import from babel config
2. Remove related configuration in .babelrc, babel.config.js, or package.json
3. Direct imports like \`import { Button } from 'antd'\` work without the plugin

**Search pattern:** \`babel-plugin-import\`

### \`antd/dist/antd.css\` and \`antd/dist/antd.less\` removed. CSS-in-JS generates styles automatically.

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

Remove the global CSS/Less import. Styles are now injected via CSS-in-JS automatically.

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
import 'antd/dist/antd.css';
// or
import 'antd/dist/antd.less';
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
// No global import needed — styles are auto-injected
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`import\\s+['"]antd/dist/antd\\.(css|less)['"]\`

### IE browser is no longer supported. v5 uses CSS-in-JS and modern CSS features.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

If your project needs IE support, you cannot upgrade to v5. Consider using @ant-design/cssinjs StyleProvider for :where selector compatibility with older browsers.

## Modal

### Prop \`visible\` renamed to \`open\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

Search for \`<Modal\` with \`visible\` prop and rename to \`open\`. Also applies to Modal.confirm, Modal.info, etc.

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Modal visible={show} onCancel={onClose}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Modal open={show} onCancel={onClose}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Modal[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

### Static methods \`Modal.confirm()\` etc. deprecated. Use \`App.useApp()\` hook instead.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

Same pattern as message/notification — use App.useApp() to get modal instance.

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
import { Modal } from 'antd';
Modal.confirm({ title: 'Sure?' });
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
import { App } from 'antd';
const MyComponent = () => {
  const { modal } = App.useApp();
  modal.confirm({ title: 'Sure?' });
};
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`\\bModal\\.(confirm|info|success|error|warning)\\(\`

## Drawer

### Prop \`visible\` renamed to \`open\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Drawer visible={show} onClose={onClose}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Drawer open={show} onClose={onClose}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Drawer[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

### Drawer \`style\` and \`className\` now apply to the panel node. Use \`rootStyle\` and \`rootClassName\` for the wrapper.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

In v5, Drawer \`style\` and \`className\` are migrated to the Drawer panel node.
If you were using them to style the wrapper/mask, replace with \`rootStyle\` and \`rootClassName\`.

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Drawer className="my-drawer" style={{ zIndex: 1000 }}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Drawer rootClassName="my-drawer" rootStyle={{ zIndex: 1000 }}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Drawer[^>]*\\b(style|className)\\s*=\`

## Tooltip

### Prop \`visible\` renamed to \`open\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Tooltip visible={show}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Tooltip open={show}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Tooltip[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

## Popover

### Prop \`visible\` renamed to \`open\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Popover visible={show}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Popover open={show}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Popover[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

## Popconfirm

### Prop \`visible\` renamed to \`open\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Popconfirm visible={show}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Popconfirm open={show}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Popconfirm[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

## Dropdown

### Prop \`visible\` renamed to \`open\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Dropdown visible={show}>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Dropdown open={show}>
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Dropdown[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

## Tag

### Prop \`visible\` removed. Use conditional rendering instead.

**BREAKING** | 📝 manual

Replace \`visible\` prop with conditional rendering using \`{condition && <Tag>...</Tag>}\`.

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Tag visible={show}>Tag</Tag>
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
{show && <Tag>Tag</Tag>}
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Tag[^>]*\\bvisible\\b\`

## Select

### Prop \`dropdownClassName\` renamed to \`popupClassName\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Select dropdownClassName="my-dropdown" />
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Select popupClassName="my-dropdown" />
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Select[^>]*\\bdropdownClassName\\b\`

### Prop \`dropdownMatchSelectWidth\` renamed to \`popupMatchSelectWidth\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Select dropdownMatchSelectWidth={false} />
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Select popupMatchSelectWidth={false} />
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<Select[^>]*\\bdropdownMatchSelectWidth\\b\`

## TreeSelect

### Prop \`dropdownClassName\` renamed to \`popupClassName\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<TreeSelect dropdownClassName="my-dropdown" />
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<TreeSelect popupClassName="my-dropdown" />
\`\`\`

**Search pattern:** \`<TreeSelect[^>]*\\bdropdownClassName\\b\`

## Cascader

### Prop \`dropdownClassName\` renamed to \`popupClassName\`

**BREAKING** | 🔧 auto-fixable

**Before:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Cascader dropdownClassName="my-dropdown" />
\`\`\`

**After:**
\`\`\`tsx
<Cascader popupClassName="my-dropdown" />
